sieve /sɪv/

(sieving,sieved,sieves) 

1. N-COUNT A sieve is a tool used for separating solids from liquids or larger pieces of something from smaller pieces. It consists of a metal or plastic ring with a wire or plastic net underneath, which the liquid or smaller pieces pass through. 筛子; 过滤器 

例： Press the raspberries through a fine sieve to form a puree. 用一把细筛子把黑莓压榨成浓汁。 

2. V-T When you sieve a substance, you put it through a sieve. 筛; 过滤 

例： Cream the margarine in a small bowl, then sieve the powdered sugar into it. 把人造黄油在小碗里搅成糊状，然后把糖粉筛入其中。

